Certainly! Here's the `populate` method with added log statements for debugging purposes:

```java
private void populate(FTPFile[] source_list_files, boolean include_folder, String initialPath) {
    Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Starting populate method with " + source_list_files.length + " files");

    Stack<Pair<FTPFile, String>> stack = new Stack<>();
    for (FTPFile f : source_list_files) {
        stack.push(new Pair<>(f, initialPath));
    }
    Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Initial stack size: " + stack.size());

    while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
        if (isCancelled()) {
            Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Operation cancelled");
            return;
        }

        Pair<FTPFile, String> pair = stack.pop();
        FTPFile f = pair.first;
        String path = pair.second;

        if (f == null) {
            Log.w("ViewModelFileCount", "Null FTPFile encountered, skipping");
            continue;
        }

        Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Processing file: " + f.getName() + " at path: " + path);

        int no_of_files = 0;
        long size_of_files = 0L;

        if (f.isDirectory()) {
            Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Processing directory: " + f.getName());
            try {
                String name = f.getName();
                String newPath = Global.CONCATENATE_PARENT_CHILD_PATH(path, name);
                FtpClientRepository ftpClientRepository = FtpClientRepository.getInstance(FtpDetailsViewModel.FTP_POJO);
                FTPClient ftpClient = ftpClientRepository.getFtpClient();
                FTPFile[] subFiles = ftpClient.listFiles(newPath);
                Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Subdirectory " + name + " contains " + subFiles.length + " files");
                for (FTPFile subFile : subFiles) {
                    stack.push(new Pair<>(subFile, newPath));
                }
                ftpClientRepository.releaseFtpClient(ftpClient);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Log.e("ViewModelFileCount", "Error processing directory: " + f.getName(), e);
            }
            if (include_folder) {
                no_of_files++;
                Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Including folder in count");
            }
        } else {
            no_of_files++;
            size_of_files += f.getSize();
            Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "File: " + f.getName() + ", Size: " + f.getSize());
        }

        cumulative_no_of_files += no_of_files;
        total_no_of_files.postValue(cumulative_no_of_files);
        total_size_of_files += size_of_files;
        size_of_files_formatted.postValue(FileUtil.humanReadableByteCount(total_size_of_files));

        Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Cumulative files: " + cumulative_no_of_files + ", Total size: " + total_size_of_files);
    }

    Log.d("ViewModelFileCount", "Populate method completed");
}
```

These log statements will help you track the progress of the method, including:
- The start and end of the method
- The number of files being processed initially
- Each file being processed, including its name and path
- Directory processing, including the number of files in each subdirectory
- File sizes for non-directory files
- Running totals of file count and size
- Any errors encountered while processing directories

